5) Return a compact table with columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, global_p95, global_p5, full_count, points_in_window, anomaly_count_in_window, earliest_anomaly_timestamp, earliest_anomaly_value, sample_anomaly_values (list up to 5 with timestamps). Limit returned rows to the top 20 component-KPIs ranked by anomaly_count_in_window (descending). Keep output concise and JSON-serializable.
